<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,258,1975]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,1266,1291]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Remarks:</emphasis>
The nominate species was originally described by Bolivar (1899) from Binboğa Mountains (
<collectingRegion box="[158,346,1302,1327]" country="Turkey" name="Kahramanmaras" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Kahramanmaraş</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[361,446,1302,1327]" name="Turkey" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Turkey</collectingCountry>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="zonatus Bolivar" authorityYear="1899" box="[468,614,1303,1326]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Poecilimon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="zonatus" subSpecies="zonatus">
<emphasis box="[468,614,1303,1326]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">P. z. zonatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
reveals a fragmented distribution in the North-South direction at high altitudes of the mountains of Anatolian diagonal and relatively high plateaus of northern part of Taurus mountains in the East-West direction. The additional faunistic records of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="zonatus Bolivar" authorityYear="1899" box="[882,1027,1375,1398]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Poecilimon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="zonatus" subSpecies="zonatus">
<emphasis box="[882,1027,1375,1398]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">P. z. zonatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were documented by Çıplak 
<emphasis box="[1376,1436,1374,1399]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">et al.</emphasis>
(1996), 
<bibRefCitation box="[239,417,1410,1435]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" refId="ref25524" refString="Karabag, T. (1958) The Orthoptera fauna of Turkey. A synonymic and distributional catalogue of Turkish Orthoptera. Ankara Universitesi, Fen Fakultesi Yayinlari, Ankara, 198 pp." type="book">Karabağ (1958)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation box="[429,622,1410,1435]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" refId="ref26123" refString="Mol, A., Taylan, M. S., Demir, E. &amp; Sirin, D. (2016) Contribution to the knowledge of Ensifera (Insecta: Orthoptera) fauna of Turkey. Journal of the Entomological Research Society, 18, 75 - 98." type="journal article">
Mol 
<emphasis box="[483,539,1410,1435]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">et al.</emphasis>
(2016)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation box="[634,805,1411,1435]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" refId="ref26405" refString="Ramme, W. (1931) Beitrage zur Kenntnis der palaearktischen Orthopterenfauna (Tettig. et Acrid.). Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin, 17, 165 - 200." type="journal article">Ramme (1931)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation box="[816,1055,1410,1435]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" refId="ref26943" refString="Sevgili, H., Demirsoy, A. &amp; Durmus, Y. (2012 b) Orthoptera fauna of Kemaliye (Erzincan). Hacettepe Journal of Biology and Chemistry, Special Issue, 317 - 335." type="book chapter">
Sevgili 
<emphasis box="[902,958,1410,1435]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">et al.</emphasis>
(2012b)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation box="[1067,1234,1411,1435]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" refId="ref27258" refString="Uvarov, B. P. (1917) Orthoptera of Caucasia and adjacent countries. II. Diagnosis of new species and varieties from the collection of the Caucasian museum. Bulletin Museum Caucase, 11, 281 - 298." type="journal article">Uvarov (1917)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation box="[1293,1432,1410,1435]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" refId="ref27416" refString="Unal, M. (2010) Phaneropterinae (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae) from Turkey and the Middle East II. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 136, 125 - 183. https: // doi. org / 10.3157 / 061.136.0203" type="journal article">Ünal (2010)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation box="[151,322,1446,1471]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" refId="ref26474" refString="Ramme, W. (1951) Zur Systematik, Faunistik und Biologie der Orthopteren von Sudost Europa und Vorderasien. Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum, Berlin, 27, 1 - 432, pls. 1 - 39." type="journal article">Ramme (1951)</bibRefCitation>
identified the specimens collected by Dr. O. Schwarz from the Sandras mountain (
<collectingRegion box="[1288,1364,1446,1471]" country="Turkey" name="Mugla" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Muğla</collectingRegion>
) as 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Poecilimon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zonatus">P. zonatus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
In this research, the samples studied by Ramme were not studied. However, it should be noted that this small population from the Datça Peninsula near the seashore and the populations outside the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sevgili &amp; Şirin &amp; Heller &amp; Lemonnier-Darcemont" authorityYear="2018" box="[1191,1307,1518,1543]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Poecilimon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salmani">
<emphasis box="[1191,1307,1518,1543]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">P. salmani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that spread around the 
<collectingRegion box="[282,462,1554,1579]" country="Turkey" name="Mugla" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Muğla province</collectingRegion>
may belong to the newly described subspecies. The new subspecies is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sevgili &amp; Şirin &amp; Heller &amp; Lemonnier-Darcemont" authorityYear="2018" box="[212,327,1590,1615]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Poecilimon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salmani">
<emphasis box="[212,327,1590,1615]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">P. salmani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is known to inhabit the areas of Fethiye and Dalyan and is described as a new species in this study by the differences of the shape of the apical part of male cerci, the shape of gonangulum and lamella in female and colour pattern of tergites in both sexes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,258,1975]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
The syllable pattern of the calling song is quite similar to that of the macrosyllables of 
<taxonomicName box="[1194,1341,1700,1723]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Poecilimon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variicercis">
<emphasis box="[1194,1341,1700,1723]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">P. variicercis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the whole song pattern of 
<taxonomicName box="[401,546,1735,1758]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Poecilimon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variicercis">
<emphasis box="[401,546,1735,1758]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">P. variicercis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows significant differences from this species (see 
<figureCitation box="[1136,1273,1734,1759]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 36" captionStart-1="FIGURE 37" captionStartId-0="44.[151,250,1983,2005]" captionStartId-1="45.[151,250,1724,1746]" captionTargetBox-0="[352,1232,194,1925]" captionTargetBox-1="[326,1253,207,1683]" captionTargetId-0="figure@44.[352,1232,193,1949]" captionTargetId-1="figure@45.[302,1284,193,1702]" captionTargetPageId-0="44" captionTargetPageId-1="45" captionText-0="FIGURE 36. The oscillograms and spectral view of the male calling songs of P. variicercis." captionText-1="FIGURE 37. The oscillograms and spectral view of the male calling songs of P. zonatus datca and P.vodnensis." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/1242403/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/1242405/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Figs. 36–37</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,258,1975]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
The new subspecies was found together with some orthopterans such as 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName authorityName="in Heller" authorityYear="1988" box="[1029,1340,1770,1795]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Poecilimon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanctipauli" subGenus="Poecilimon">Poecilimon (P.) sanctipauli</taxonomicName>
, P. (H.). hamatus, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Maran" authorityYear="1953" box="[260,436,1806,1831]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Eupholidoptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Eupholidoptera</taxonomicName>
sp.
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Karabag" authorityYear="1953" box="[529,801,1806,1831]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Orchamus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="yersini" subSpecies="davisi">
<emphasis box="[529,801,1806,1831]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Orchamus yersini davisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<typeStatus box="[870,918,1807,1831]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,258,1975]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
This species has not been assessed for the 
<collectionCode box="[674,742,1843,1867]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">IUCN</collectionCode>
Red List (2017–3). The distribution of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sevgili &amp; Şirin &amp; Heller &amp; Lemonnier-Darcemont" authorityYear="2018" box="[1228,1410,1842,1867]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Poecilimon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="zonatus" subSpecies="datca">
<emphasis box="[1228,1410,1842,1867]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">P. zonatus datca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is highly restricted and its habitats are under the threat by anthropogenic effects, such as stubble fire, over-use of pesticides in agriculture, touristic activities and grazing. For these reasons, the species should be considered with a Critically Endangered (B1ab(i, iii)) status on the basis of the extent of occurrence criteries of 
<collectionCode box="[1198,1270,1951,1975]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">IUCN</collectionCode>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
